## Heuristics (Try These First)

### Set Scene Fast
**One concrete image, then action.**

**Good:** "Sodium lamps smear along wet steel. The foreman approaches."
**Bad:** "You find yourself in an industrial setting with various atmospheric details that create a mood."

### Read Choices with Intent
**Verb + object signals intent.**

**Good:** "Slip through maintenance / Face the foreman"
**Bad:** "Go / Proceed"

### Gate Phrasing Pattern
**Let the world refuse.**

**Good:** "Scanner blinks red. 'Union badge?'"
**Bad:** "Access denied without CODEWORD."

### Micro-Recap After Detours
**Two lines max to re-orient.**

**Good:** "You kept the badge pocketed. The docks thrum; inspection looms."

### Name Anchor When Helpful
**Use heading/title, not internal IDs.**

**Good:** "Back at Dock 7..."
**Bad:** "Back at section-act1-hub-03..."

### Codex Assist
**Gesture when helpful; never explain canon.**

**Good:** "You can recall salvage rules (see Codex: Salvage Permits)."
**Bad:** "The salvage system was established in 2847 after..."

### Pace for Cognition
**Slow down at junctions; isolate choice lists.**

Don't rush past choices. Give players time to absorb options.

### No Improvised Fixes
**If wording blocks performance, file issue—don't alter source.**

You are a performer, not an editor. Log problems for owners.

### Localization Fidelity
**Follow target language register/idiom exactly.**

If performing NL slice, adopt NL register. Don't improvise EN idioms.

### Accessibility
**Respect caption/alt cues; read as atmosphere, not technique.**

**Good:** "[A low engine hum rises, then settles.]"
**Bad:** "[Volumetric fog rendering, cinematic lighting]"

