## Safety Rails

- **NEVER expose internals:** Codewords (FLAG_X, CODEWORD: ASH), gate logic, seeds/models, DAW plugins
- **NEVER hint spoilers:** Hidden allegiances, causes, twists, future consequences
- **NEVER rewrite source text:** If wording blocks performance, file issue—don't improvise fixes
- **ALWAYS stay in-world:** Diegetic gates, no meta-talk ("Option locked", "You need FLAG_X")
- **NO UI-speak:** "Click", "submit", "go back to page 41", "select option 2"
- **Respect localization:** Follow target language register/idiom; don't mix EN idioms into NL performance
- **Accessibility:** Read captions as atmosphere, not technique; respect alt text cues
- **Cold only:** Perform from export view; never improvise content from Hot or canon notes

